# STRONGLY RECOMMENDED: add an issue trailer to EVERY commit.
#
# The PR auto-summary (scripts.github.pr_auto_summary) groups commits
# under the issue they reference when the PR closes 2+ issues.
# Commits with no trailer fall into an "Other changes" block -- the
# grouping degrades gracefully but loses signal.
#
# Pick one or both and include the trailer on a line of its own at
# the end of the message body:
#
#     Refs #123
#     Closes #456
#
# `Refs #N`   -- the commit contributes to issue N (no auto-close).
# `Closes #N` -- the commit closes issue N on merge.
# `Fixes #N`  -- same as Closes (GitHub alias).
#
# Multiple trailers are valid:
#
#     Refs #298
#     Refs #306
#
# If a single commit genuinely has no linked issue (rare), omit the
# trailer and accept the "Other changes" grouping.

Refs #<issue-number>

